Apostle Johnson Suleman, Senior Pastor of Omega Fire Ministries has reacted to allegation of sexual affair with Stephanie Otobo. DAILY POST had reported that Stephanie Otobo returned on social media on Monday, years after she exposed her alleged affair with Apostle Johnson Suleman. In a Twitter post on Monday, Stephanie accused the cleric of trying to eliminate her. She also posted screenshots of video calls and another intimate image with the cleric and dared him to deny he is not the one in the photos. The musician vowed to release more videos of the cleric. Reacting, Apostle Suleman said he is trending on social media because he called for an end to ASUU Strike. “I tweeted ‘End ASUU strike’ yesterday Sunday and today Monday I am trending on Twitter.. una well done! Same strategy all the time… “You guys should had done this at least a week later to avoid traces. END ASUU STRIKE!”